  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@eunjae-lee I'm not sure if it is related to this issue, but I also found that the initial `renderOptions` passed to the connector callback argument are incorrect if a range filter is set at initialisation time. For example:\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\nconnectRange((renderOptions, isFirstRender) => {\r\n    renderOptions.start[0] // Should be the initial lower bound filter if set\r\n    renderOptions.start[1] // Should be the initial upper bound filter if set\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut regardless of how I supply this state, I always get passed the range limits min/max. I have tried:\r\n1. Setting the `initialUiState`:\r\n    ```typescript\r\n    instantsearch({\r\n        // ...\r\n        initialUiState: {\r\n            [indexName]: {\r\n                range: {\r\n                    price: '150:1500',\r\n                }\r\n            },\r\n        },\r\n    })\r\n    ```\r\n2. Use state mapping with the history router:\r\n    ```typescript\r\n    routeToState(routeState: RouteState): UiState {\r\n        return {\r\n            [indexName]: {\r\n                range: {\r\n                    price: '150:1500'\r\n                },\r\n            },\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    ```\r\n\r\nAm I missing something?\r\nThanks in advance!\r\n\r\n**EDIT**\r\nThis also happens outside controlled mode.\r\n\r\n",
    "created_at": "2021-01-19T09:45:17Z",
